---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterForm from '../components/NewsletterForm.astro';
import { companies } from '../data/companies';

const featuredCompanies = companies.filter((c) => c.featured);
---

<BaseLayout
  title="David Henzel"
  description="David Henzel helps people find their purpose and build systems for a life they love. Serial entrepreneur, author, and creator of the Love Not Fear operating system."
>

  <!-- Opening essay -->
  <section class="pt-16 pb-0">
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-foreground mb-5 border-l-2 border-accent pl-4">
      Every decision in life, you make out of love or out of fear.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      A yoga teacher said that to me years ago, and it rewired everything. Not gradually. Immediately. I started seeing it everywhere: in the way I ran my companies, in the way I treated my team, in the way I showed up at home. Most of what I thought were rational business decisions were actually fear dressed up in a spreadsheet.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      I've been building companies for over 25 years. I started as a teenager in Wiesbaden, Germany, painfully shy, running a business I was barely brave enough to talk about. I lived in Los Angeles for years before moving to Bodrum, Turkey. I've never had a real job. What I've had instead is a long, messy education in figuring out what actually matters.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      The turning point wasn't a business win. It was my wife's breast cancer diagnosis. She's fine today. But lying awake at 3am, I realized something that changed the trajectory of everything: <strong class="text-foreground">the biggest risk isn't failing at something new. The biggest risk is succeeding at something that doesn't matter.</strong>
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      We had a successful exit. It was a great outcome. But instead of doing the same thing again, I started building a portfolio of companies around what actually mattered to me.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      Now I run a <a href="/companies" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">portfolio of companies</a> with over 500 employees. But the thing I care most about is <a href="https://lovenotfear.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">Love Not Fear</a>, an operating system for living and leading with purpose. Four pillars: find your purpose, define your values, craft your vision, build your habits. We use it with <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/students" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">students</a> trying to figure out what to do with their lives, <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/entrepreneurs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">entrepreneurs</a> who've lost the plot, and <a href="https://lnfpeople.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">companies</a> that want to hire and lead differently.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-2">
      I'm also writing a book about all of this. It's not a self-help book. It's a self-leadership book. There's a difference.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-secondary mb-5">
      Want to know when it comes out? <button onclick="document.getElementById('book-signup').classList.toggle('hidden')" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-none p-0 text-sm font-normal">Sign up here</button> and I'll let you know.
    </p>
    <div id="book-signup" class="hidden mb-5">
      <NewsletterForm id="book-inline" compact />
      <p class="text-xs text-secondary/50 mt-1">No spam. Just the book announcement.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-secondary/60 mb-0">
      Featured in Forbes, Inc., Fast Company, HuffPost, VentureBeat, The Next Web.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-t border-accent/25 my-12" />

  <!-- What I believe -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-6">What I believe</h2>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      Most personal development is backwards. People set goals, build habits, and grind, then wonder why they feel empty when they hit the number. That's because they skipped the foundation. You can't build a system for your life if you don't know what your life is for.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      Purpose comes first. Not passion. Purpose. Passion is what you enjoy. Purpose is what you'd do even when it's hard. Once you know that, values become your filter. Vision becomes your direction. Habits become your engine. In that order.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      I believe most fear-based decisions look rational on the surface. Staying in a job you've outgrown because "the market is tough." Not raising prices because "customers might leave." Not having the hard conversation because "the timing isn't right." These feel like logic. They're not. They're fear wearing a reasonable mask.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      I believe you should build companies that make the world slightly less broken, not slightly more optimized. I believe the best leaders are the ones who've done the inner work. I believe you can be ambitious and kind at the same time, and that anyone who tells you otherwise is protecting their own cynicism.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      I believe simplicity is a discipline, not a style. The hardest thing in business, and in life, is saying no to good things so you can say yes to the right things.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-t border-accent/25 my-12" />

  <!-- Values -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-6">Values</h2>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      <span class="font-semibold text-accent">1. First Things First.</span> Always prioritize health and your loved ones. If it's not a "FUCK YES," it's a "NO."
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      <span class="font-semibold text-accent">2. Own It.</span> Always do your best. Be impeccable with your word. Do not complain or blame. Find solutions.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      <span class="font-semibold text-accent">3. Create Impact.</span> Enrich the lives of everybody we come in touch with. Don't take things personal. Do not make assumptions.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-5">
      <span class="font-semibold text-accent">4. Unconditional Love.</span> Make decisions out of love, not fear.
    </p>

    <p class="text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
      <span class="font-semibold text-accent">5. Simplicity.</span> Be Authentic. Only do and buy things that matter.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      Want to define your own? I built a free AI tool that walks you through it. <a href="https://community.lovenotfear.com/c/define-your-personal-core-values" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">Discover your core values here</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr class="border-t border-accent/25 my-12" />

  <!-- Companies -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent mb-6">Companies</h2>

    {featuredCompanies.map((company) => (
      <p class="mb-3.5 leading-relaxed">
        <a href={company.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="font-semibold text-accent underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent transition-colors">{company.name}</a>
        <span class="text-secondary/40 mx-1">&middot;</span>
        <span class="text-sm text-secondary" set:html={company.description.replace(/<a[^>]*>/g, '').replace(/<\/a>/g, '')} />
      </p>
    ))}

    <p class="mt-6">
      <a href="/companies" class="text-sm text-accent transition-colors underline underline-offset-3 decoration-accent/30 hover:decoration-accent">See all companies</a>
    </p>
  </section>



</BaseLayout>
